## 6. Testing Database Queries

### In-Memory SQLite for Tests
```typescript
import Database from 'better-sqlite3';

let testDb: Database.Database;

beforeEach(() => {
  testDb = new Database(':memory:');
  initSchema(testDb);
});

afterEach(() => {
  testDb.close();
});
```

---

## 7. Best Practices

### Test Behavior, Not Implementation
```typescript
// ❌ Testing implementation
expect(store.upsertLaunch).toHaveBeenCalledTimes(1);

// ✅ Testing behavior
const launches = store.getLaunches();
expect(launches).toContainEqual(expect.objectContaining({ name: 'test-launch' }));
```

### Keep Tests Independent
Each test sets up its own state and doesn't rely on other tests.

### Clear Test Names
```typescript
// ❌ Vague
it('works', () => {});

// ✅ Descriptive
it('should return empty array when no launches match the filter', () => {});
```

### Arrange-Act-Assert
```typescript
it('should compute pass rate correctly', () => {
  // Arrange
  const launch = createMockLaunch({ passed: 80, total: 100 });

  // Act
  const rate = computePassRate(launch);

  // Assert
  expect(rate).toBe(0.8);
});
```

---

## 8. Running Tests

```bash
# When test runner is added:
npm test                         # Run all tests
npm test -- --watch              # Watch mode
npm test path/to/file.test.ts    # Specific file
```

---

## 9. Checklist

### Unit Test Checklist
- [ ] Tests behavior, not implementation
- [ ] Covers happy path
- [ ] Covers error cases
- [ ] Covers edge cases (empty data, null, boundaries)
- [ ] Independent (no test order dependency)
- [ ] Properly mocks external dependencies
- [ ] Cleans up after itself
